33#include <drm/drmP.h>

35struct vbt_header {
36 u8 signature[20]; /**< Always starts with 'VBT$' */
37 u16 version; /**< decimal */
38 u16 header_size; /**< in bytes */
39 u16 vbt_size; /**< in bytes */
40 u8 vbt_checksum;
41 u8 reserved0;
42 u32 bdb_offset; /**< from beginning of VBT */
43 u32 aim_offset[4]; /**< from beginning of VBT */
44} __packed;
45
46struct bdb_header {
47 u8 signature[16]; /**< Always 'BIOS_DATA_BLOCK' */
48 u16 version; /**< decimal */
49 u16 header_size; /**< in bytes */
50 u16 bdb_size; /**< in bytes */
51} __packed;
52
53/* strictly speaking, this is a "skip" block, but it has interesting info */
54struct vbios_data {
55 u8 type; /* 0 == desktop, 1 == mobile */
56 u8 relstage;
57 u8 chipset;
58 u8 lvds_present:1;
59 u8 tv_present:1;
60 u8 rsvd2:6; /* finish byte */
61 u8 rsvd3[4];
62 u8 signon[155];
63 u8 copyright[61];
64 u16 code_segment;
65 u8 dos_boot_mode;
66 u8 bandwidth_percent;
67 u8 rsvd4; /* popup memory size */
68 u8 resize_pci_bios;
69 u8 rsvd5; /* is crt already on ddc2 */
70} __packed;
71
72/*
73 * There are several types of BIOS data blocks (BDBs), each block has
74 * an ID and size in the first 3 bytes (ID in first, size in next 2).
75 * Known types are listed below.
76 */
77#define BDB_GENERAL_FEATURES 1
78#define BDB_GENERAL_DEFINITIONS 2
79#define BDB_OLD_TOGGLE_LIST 3
80#define BDB_MODE_SUPPORT_LIST 4
81#define BDB_GENERIC_MODE_TABLE 5
82#define BDB_EXT_MMIO_REGS 6
83#define BDB_SWF_IO 7
84#define BDB_SWF_MMIO 8
85#define BDB_PSR 9
86#define BDB_MODE_REMOVAL_TABLE 10
87#define BDB_CHILD_DEVICE_TABLE 11
88#define BDB_DRIVER_FEATURES 12
89#define BDB_DRIVER_PERSISTENCE 13
90#define BDB_EXT_TABLE_PTRS 14
91#define BDB_DOT_CLOCK_OVERRIDE 15
92#define BDB_DISPLAY_SELECT 16
93/* 17 rsvd */
94#define BDB_DRIVER_ROTATION 18
95#define BDB_DISPLAY_REMOVE 19
96#define BDB_OEM_CUSTOM 20
97#define BDB_EFP_LIST 21 /* workarounds for VGA hsync/vsync */
98#define BDB_SDVO_LVDS_OPTIONS 22
99#define BDB_SDVO_PANEL_DTDS 23
100#define BDB_SDVO_LVDS_PNP_IDS 24
101#define BDB_SDVO_LVDS_POWER_SEQ 25
102#define BDB_TV_OPTIONS 26
103#define BDB_EDP 27
104#define BDB_LVDS_OPTIONS 40
105#define BDB_LVDS_LFP_DATA_PTRS 41
106#define BDB_LVDS_LFP_DATA 42
107#define BDB_LVDS_BACKLIGHT 43
108#define BDB_LVDS_POWER 44
109#define BDB_MIPI_CONFIG 52
110#define BDB_MIPI_SEQUENCE 53
111#define BDB_SKIP 254 /* VBIOS private block, ignore */
112
113struct bdb_general_features {
114 /* bits 1 */
115 u8 panel_fitting:2;
116 u8 flexaim:1;
117 u8 msg_enable:1;
118 u8 clear_screen:3;
119 u8 color_flip:1;
120
121 /* bits 2 */
122 u8 download_ext_vbt:1;
123 u8 enable_ssc:1;
124 u8 ssc_freq:1;
125 u8 enable_lfp_on_override:1;
126 u8 disable_ssc_ddt:1;
127 u8 rsvd7:1;
128 u8 display_clock_mode:1;
129 u8 rsvd8:1; /* finish byte */
130
131 /* bits 3 */
132 u8 disable_smooth_vision:1;
133 u8 single_dvi:1;
134 u8 rsvd9:1;
135 u8 fdi_rx_polarity_inverted:1;
136 u8 rsvd10:4; /* finish byte */
137
138 /* bits 4 */
139 u8 legacy_monitor_detect;
140
141 /* bits 5 */
142 u8 int_crt_support:1;
143 u8 int_tv_support:1;
144 u8 int_efp_support:1;
145 u8 dp_ssc_enb:1; /* PCH attached eDP supports SSC */
146 u8 dp_ssc_freq:1; /* SSC freq for PCH attached eDP */
147 u8 rsvd11:3; /* finish byte */
148} __packed;

257/* This field changes depending on the BDB version, so the most reliable way to
258 * read it is by checking the BDB version and reading the raw pointer. */
259union child_device_config {
260 /* This one is safe to be used anywhere, but the code should still check
261 * the BDB version. */
262 u8 raw[33];
263 /* This one should only be kept for legacy code. */
264 struct old_child_dev_config old;
265 /* This one should also be safe to use anywhere, even without version
266 * checks. */
267 struct common_child_dev_config common;
268} __packed;

270struct bdb_general_definitions {
271 /* DDC GPIO */
272 u8 crt_ddc_gmbus_pin;
273
274 /* DPMS bits */
275 u8 dpms_acpi:1;
276 u8 skip_boot_crt_detect:1;
277 u8 dpms_aim:1;
278 u8 rsvd1:5; /* finish byte */
279
280 /* boot device bits */
281 u8 boot_display[2];
282 u8 child_dev_size;
283
284 /*
285 * Device info:
286 * If TV is present, it'll be at devices[0].
287 * LVDS will be next, either devices[0] or [1], if present.
288 * On some platforms the number of device is 6. But could be as few as
289 * 4 if both TV and LVDS are missing.
290 * And the device num is related with the size of general definition
291 * block. It is obtained by using the following formula:
292 * number = (block_size - sizeof(bdb_general_definitions))/
293 * defs->child_dev_size;
294 */
295 uint8_t devices[0];
296} __packed;

301struct bdb_lvds_options {
302 u8 panel_type;
303 u8 rsvd1;
304 /* LVDS capabilities, stored in a dword */
305 u8 pfit_mode:2;
306 u8 pfit_text_mode_enhanced:1;
307 u8 pfit_gfx_mode_enhanced:1;
308 u8 pfit_ratio_auto:1;
309 u8 pixel_dither:1;
310 u8 lvds_edid:1;
311 u8 rsvd2:1;
312 u8 rsvd4;
313 /* LVDS Panel channel bits stored here */
314 u32 lvds_panel_channel_bits;
315 /* LVDS SSC (Spread Spectrum Clock) bits stored here. */
316 u16 ssc_bits;
317 u16 ssc_freq;
318 u16 ssc_ddt;
319 /* Panel color depth defined here */
320 u16 panel_color_depth;
321 /* LVDS panel type bits stored here */
322 u32 dps_panel_type_bits;
323 /* LVDS backlight control type bits stored here */
324 u32 blt_control_type_bits;
325} __packed;

343struct lvds_fp_timing {

345 u16 y_res;

593int intel_parse_bios(struct drm_device *dev);
594
595/*
596 * Driver<->VBIOS interaction occurs through scratch bits in
597 * GR18 & SWF*.
598 */
599
600/* GR18 bits are set on display switch and hotkey events */
601#define GR18_DRIVER_SWITCH_EN (1<<7) /* 0: VBIOS control, 1: driver control */
602#define GR18_HOTKEY_MASK 0x78 /* See also SWF4 15:0 */
603#define GR18_HK_NONE (0x0<<3)
604#define GR18_HK_LFP_STRETCH (0x1<<3)
605#define GR18_HK_TOGGLE_DISP (0x2<<3)
606#define GR18_HK_DISP_SWITCH (0x4<<3) /* see SWF14 15:0 for what to enable */
607#define GR18_HK_POPUP_DISABLED (0x6<<3)
608#define GR18_HK_POPUP_ENABLED (0x7<<3)
609#define GR18_HK_PFIT (0x8<<3)
610#define GR18_HK_APM_CHANGE (0xa<<3)
611#define GR18_HK_MULTIPLE (0xc<<3)
612#define GR18_USER_INT_EN (1<<2)
613#define GR18_A0000_FLUSH_EN (1<<1)
614#define GR18_SMM_EN (1<<0)
615
616/* Set by driver, cleared by VBIOS */
617#define SWF00_YRES_SHIFT 16
618#define SWF00_XRES_SHIFT 0
619#define SWF00_RES_MASK 0xffff
620
621/* Set by VBIOS at boot time and driver at runtime */
622#define SWF01_TV2_FORMAT_SHIFT 8
623#define SWF01_TV1_FORMAT_SHIFT 0
624#define SWF01_TV_FORMAT_MASK 0xffff
625
626#define SWF10_VBIOS_BLC_I2C_EN (1<<29)
627#define SWF10_GTT_OVERRIDE_EN (1<<28)
628#define SWF10_LFP_DPMS_OVR (1<<27) /* override DPMS on display switch */
629#define SWF10_ACTIVE_TOGGLE_LIST_MASK (7<<24)
630#define SWF10_OLD_TOGGLE 0x0
631#define SWF10_TOGGLE_LIST_1 0x1
632#define SWF10_TOGGLE_LIST_2 0x2
633#define SWF10_TOGGLE_LIST_3 0x3
634#define SWF10_TOGGLE_LIST_4 0x4
635#define SWF10_PANNING_EN (1<<23)
636#define SWF10_DRIVER_LOADED (1<<22)
637#define SWF10_EXTENDED_DESKTOP (1<<21)
638#define SWF10_EXCLUSIVE_MODE (1<<20)
639#define SWF10_OVERLAY_EN (1<<19)
640#define SWF10_PLANEB_HOLDOFF (1<<18)
641#define SWF10_PLANEA_HOLDOFF (1<<17)

915/* Block 52 contains MIPI configuration block
916 * 6 * bdb_mipi_config, followed by 6 pps data
917 * block below

919 * all delays has a unit of 100us
920 */

929struct bdb_mipi_config {

932} __packed;
